  "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes [#94](https://github.com/link-foundation/box/issues/94): the `box-dind`\nnested daemon boots with an **empty image store**, so a fresh container re-pulls\nimages the host already has (the classic Docker-in-Docker cache pitfall).\n\nThis PR seeds the inner daemon at startup via two complementary paths, both\n**daemon-gated**, **idempotent** (skip images already present), and **non-fatal**\n(a bad path / failed copy logs a warning and the shell still starts):\n\n### 1. Explicit preload\n| Variable | Behavior |\n| --- | --- |\n| `DIND_PRELOAD_TARBALL` | Space-separated `docker save` tarballs and/or directories of `*.tar`, `docker load`-ed into the inner daemon. Zero-network host-image reuse. |\n| `DIND_PRELOAD_IMAGES` | Space-separated references to `docker pull`, skipping any already present. |\n\n### 2. Host-image passthrough — on by default, opt-out-able (issue follow-up)\nAddresses the owner's follow-up: *\"by default add host-image passthrough … possible\nto turn it off … do passthrough only for images that are available in docker hub\nand so on, so these are safe from tokens and baked in configuration … also have an\noption to pass through them all.\"*\n\n| Variable | Default | Behavior |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `DIND_HOST_PASSTHROUGH` | `public` | `public`: copy only host images carrying a `RepoDigest` from an allowlisted public registry (freely re-pullable → no local secrets/credentials leak). `all`: copy every tagged image. `off`/`0`/`false`/`no`: disable. |\n| `DIND_HOST_DOCKER_SOCK` | `/var/run/host-docker.sock` | Path to the mounted *host* Docker socket. A **non-default** path, mounted read-only, used only to seed images — the inner daemon keeps its own isolated `/var/run/docker.sock`. |\n| `DIND_HOST_PASSTHROUGH_REGISTRIES` | common public registries | Allowlist treated as \"public\" in `public` mode. |\n\nEnable it by mounting the host socket; otherwise it is a **quiet no-op**, so the\nnormal `--privileged` run is unchanged:\n\n```bash\ndocker run -d --privileged \\\n  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/host-docker.sock:ro \\\n  --name box-dind konard/box-dind sleep infinity\n```\n\n**Why this preserves isolation (issue #80):** the host socket is read only at\nstartup to *seed* images and is deliberately **not** mounted at\n`/var/run/docker.sock`. The inner daemon stays the container's runtime, so the\nper-container `docker ps` scoping is intact and we never adopt the\nDocker-outside-of-Docker security model the project rejects. **Why `public` is the\nsafe default:** a `RepoDigest` from a public registry proves the image is freely\nre-pullable, so copying it leaks no build secrets and needs no credential; local\nbuilds (no RepoDigest) and private-registry images are excluded unless you opt into\n`all`.\n\n## How to reproduce / verify\n\n- **Isolated unit test** — runs anywhere (the CI sandbox is `vfs`-only and cannot\n  build the overlay-backed dind image): `bash experiments/preload-unit-test.sh`\n  sources the real entrypoint and drives load/pull/skip/daemon-down/no-op plus the\n  passthrough branches (public filter, `all`, skip-present, `off`, registry\n  detection) with a mock `docker` and a **real AF_UNIX socket** → 26 assertions, all pass.\n- **Integration example** (CI `pr-test-dind`, privileged):\n  `tests/dind/example-preload-images.sh` asserts the single-file and directory\n  tarball forms seed the inner daemon, `DIND_PRELOAD_IMAGES` skips the redundant\n  pull, and — using a throwaway second dind-box as a controlled host daemon —\n  `all` mode copies a local fixture while `public` mode correctly refuses it\n  (no RepoDigest). Wired into CI alongside the other documented dind examples.\n\n## CI/CD review (PR #95 follow-up request)\n\n- **\"Skip CI/CD when a new commit arrives, for both main and PRs\"** — already\n  satisfied: both `release.yml` and `measure-disk-space.yml` use\n  `concurrency: { group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}, cancel-in-progress: true }`.\n  The per-`github.ref` group cancels superseded runs on PR branches (each PR has\n  its own group) **and** on `main`.\n  - **Deliberate divergence from the templates:** the `js`/`rust`/`python`/`csharp`\n    pipeline templates use `cancel-in-progress: ${{ github.ref != 'refs/heads/main' }}`\n    to *protect* main-branch releases from mid-flight cancellation. Box uses the\n    **unconditional** form per the explicit \"both main and PRs\" request. Trade-off:\n    a new push to `main` can cancel an in-progress release on `main`. If protecting\n    releases is preferred, switch to the conditional form — flag if you'd like that.\n- **Template comparison** (full workflow file tree across all four templates): the\n  only shared CI gap found is that the **js** template's `links.yml` is missing a\n  `concurrency:` block its sibling workflows have. Reported upstream as authorized:\n  **link-foundation/js-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template#73**.\n\n## Files changed\n- `ubuntu/24.04/dind/dind-entrypoint.sh` — preload hook + host passthrough + env docs.\n- `tests/dind/example-preload-images.sh` — executable example (CI), incl. passthrough.\n- `experiments/preload-unit-test.sh` — isolated branch coverage (preload + passthrough).\n- `docs/dind/USAGE.md`, `README.md`, `docs/case-studies/issue-94/CASE-STUDY.md` — docs.\n- `.changeset/dind-preload-images.md` — `bump: minor` (release trigger; VERSION is\n  bumped by CI, not manually).\n\n\n\nFixes #94",
